        "stdout": "Usage: vt-loadtest archive [--path <path>] [--exclude-urls-regex <regex>...] [--output <folder path>] [--browser] [--browser-errors] [--threads <count>] [--delay] [--verbose] [--spider] [--domain <example.com>] [--domain-alts <www.example.com>...] [--cross-domain] [--ignore-content-type] [--content-search-include <main-content>] [--content-search-exclude <exclude-content>] [--content-search-terms <search term>...] [--only-save-if-term-found] [--user-agent <user-agent>] [--header <header>...] [--help]\r\n\r\nSave the HTML of pages.\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  -p, --path <path>                             URL to a sitemap or file path to a URL list. If file path ends in \".xml\", file is assumed a local copy of a sitemap. (Required)\r\n  --exclude-urls-regex <regex>...               Exclude URL paths using regular expressions.\r\n  -o, --output <folder path>                    File path to save output to. (Required)\r\n  -b, --browser                                 Use browser (Puppeteer) to fully render pages, including JS. Otherwise only HTML source is considered.\r\n  -e, --browser-errors                          Log browser console errors.\r\n  -t, --threads <count>                         Number of concurrent threads to make requests. (Default: 2)\r\n  -d, --delay                                   Add delay between requests.\r\n  -v, --verbose                                 Show more logging.\r\n  --spider                                      Enable spider (find local pages linked from other pages). Limited to the primary domain or equivalent.\r\n  --domain <example.com>                        Primary domain to archive.\r\n  --domain-alts <www.example.com>...            Primary domain equivalents.\r\n  --cross-domain                                Scan cross domain redirects. Note that spider link finding is still limited to only the primary domain.\r\n  --ignore-content-type                         Ignore the Content-Type header when archiving. Otherwise only text/html is saved.\r\n  --content-search-include <main-content>       Only search content within this CSS selector. For example, body or main. Whole document is saved by default.\r\n  --content-search-exclude <exclude-content>    Exclude elements from the include content that match this CSS selector.\r\n  --content-search-terms <search term>...       Search content for specific terms. Results are output to the CSV.\r\n  --only-save-if-term-found                     Only save content if one of the search terms is found.\r\n  --user-agent <user-agent>                     User-Agent to use for requests.\r\n  --header <header>...                          Custom headers to include in requests. Format: \"Key: Value\".\r\n  -h, --help                                    Show help message",
